reviews.content:
Story-line => 4.5/5 ( The story-line is unique. I liked the way everything unfolds. I like the journey and the ending. But there are some loose ends. );
Acting => 5/5 ( The voice acting should get a lot of appreciation here. );
Directing => 4/5 (The directing in cannon episodes were top-notch but filler episodes were kinda boring. Personally I like the directing in Season 2 the most.);
Animation => 5/5 (It was more than enough for the show. I would suggest watching a 1080p version if you want to get the best experience.);
Screenplay => 4/5 (The screenplay in Season 1 was sloppy. But it was awesome in Season 2 & 3. Season 2 was the best in this case also.);
Personal Recommendation => 4.5/5 (I loved watching the whole show and I would ask everyone to watch this to get a different kind of experience.);
Most Favorite Character => Zuko (He got the best character development in the whole series. I liked this character because I felt like I could relate to him. Hats off to the directors and writers to build this wonderful character.);I would have loved more of the Order of White Lotus. But, I guess that's how great shows end. Even if it's finished, the audience wants more. I am gonna watch the sequel (The Legend of Korra) to find out more about the future of the Avatar team.
